AGI - Vincenzo&nbsp died; Augustine, the pope of the officer of the Nino State Police, killed by Cosa Nostra together with his wife Ida Castelluccio, on August 8, 1989. Vincenzo&nbsp; Augustine, born on March 22, 1937, was the courageous father, who had never resigned to the death of his son and daughter-in-law - pregnant a few months - and had immediately denounced the attempts of deceiving linked to the double murder. He had a long white beard that he said he wouldn't cut any more until the truth came out about the warrants of the double murder, the silences, and especially the deceiving of the investigation. Vincenzo continued to fight for his son even after his wife's death, Augusta Schiera, in February 2019.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Of the death of Nino and Ida - for which were many detective tracks, of which some totally deceiving - were accused three people, including the boss of Resuttana Nino Madonia, the favorite killer by Toto' Riina, who opted for the short rite and in 2021 was sentenced to life imprisonment, also confirmed on appeal on 5 October. Also that day Vincenzo - accompanied by daughters, grandchildren and his inseparable escort but without any more his wife Augusta - showed up at the justice palace of Palermo.
&nbsp;
<div </div After the sentence, Vincenzo Agostino - with his white beard and the slow but decided step facilitated by a stick - was clearly, as always: "I am satisfied because they have condemned the butcher of my son and daughter. Satisfied also for my wife, I wanted her to be there with me. Now I will remove the writing on his stone 'dead waiting for truth' and justice'. He's approaching the day I could cut the beard, because the ordinary procedure is also being completed, in case of conviction I can say that that day I can keep the promise I made on my son's grave." "Today - he had written on Facebook the month before addressing his wife - we would have celebrated 64 years of marriage. Every second without you is an agony, I miss you infinitely. I will continue to love you, always yours, Vincenzo."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The other two defendants - under trial with the ordinary rite - are the boss of the Arenella Gaetano Scotto, accused of the double aggravated murder, and Francesco Paolo Rizzuto, a friend of Nino&nbsp; Augustine, accused of aid. Also in this procedure Vincenzo - constituted civil part, assisted by lawyer Fabio Repici and with him also the daughters, grandchildren and family of Ida Castelluccio, among others - has always wanted to be present, at every hearing, despite the attacks due to age. He will assist from elsewhere in the sentence, being the trial at the final jokes: the civil parties have already discussed, on May 3 and 21 are scheduled the interventions of the defenders of the defendants and then the Court of Assis, chaired by Sergio Gulotta, should retire to the council chamber for the sentence.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Nino Augustine, the policeman who hunted the complainants
<br> Nino&nbsp;Agostino&nbsp; was an agent in service at the San Lorenzo Commissioner in Palermo who would also be part of a group that collaborated with the Secret Service for the capture of mafia latients. This would have been the cause of his death determined by What ours. The many depistages to the investigations, also came to light thanks to the perseverance of Vincenzo&nbsp; Augusta Schiera. A moment, important, in this long and tiring battle of truth, was on February 26, 2016, when in the bunker room of the Ucciardone prison there was a dramatic American recognition. Vincenzo recognized in "monkey face" Giovanni Aiello, a former police officer and considered a killer orbiting services and criminality. "I did my duty. Now - he said at the end of that day - it touches the judiciary. I recognized a monster face even though he was well made. They were in three for the confrontation, but I immediately recognized him. Like I said all these years, that face is unforgettable." Vincenzo&nbsp; Augustine, in fact, had told the magistrates that a few days before the crime in two had come to look for his son in the house of Carini, they qualified as colleagues and one had a face thrown, as a monster. "Unforgettable", in fact.&nbsp;
