AGI - Happy wonderful birthday, chaotic, difficult and seductive Rome. The &nbsp; 21 April marks the 2,777th year since the foundation of what is considered worldwide the most beautiful city of all. Many initiatives to celebrate this feast known as the "Christmas of Rome". There is a rich cultural program of meetings, guided tours, exhibitions, shows, active already from Saturday 20 and that will last until Monday 22 April. There are several 'special' events also visible on the site of the Municipality. The initiatives for the Christmas of Rome number 2.777 are promoted by Rome Capital, Assessorato alla Cultura, Superintendenza Capitolina ai Beni Culturali. Organization by Zètema Progetto Cultura.
Let's go see what the program holds. Saturday, April 20 from 20 to 22, in the Villa of Massenzio, on the fourth mile of the Via Appia Antica, you can participate in the inauguration of the new lighting created by the Capitoline Superintendency to the Cultural Heritage to enhance the monumental remains present in the approximately 20 hectares of the archaeological area and allow visitors access after sunset for special events. The new lighting system has affected the area of the dynastic mausoleum, the access path to the Villa, the towers and the prisons, allowing citizens to enjoy the evocative spectacle of the imposing imperial structures even at night. And then, tomorrow from 11 to 19, in the multifunctional space of the Sala Santa Rita, in via Montanara, next to the Teatro di Marcello, it will be possible to visit the free exhibition "La Dea Roma" by Pietro Tenerani.
<br The celebrations include visits and tours to rediscover the beauty of the city through the observation and story of works, monuments, artistic and cultural testimonies. Saturday, at the Villa di Massenzio is the event Ab Urbe condita 2024, an immersion in time and history, which will continue the next day. Thanks to the new artistic lighting you can visit the museum space until 22 (last entrance at 21.30). Visit 21 to the Museum of the Roman Republic and the Garibaldian memory April 1849: Rome prepares for the battle to discover the characters and events of the Roman Republic of 1849. The morning of tomorrow, here is the appointment at 10.15 and 11.45, at the Museum of Sculpture Antica Giovanni Barracco for the distant avi of the Latin alphabet, a guided tour with a deepening of the first graphic systems that led to the creation of the Latin alphabet. At the Carlo Bilotti Museum at the Aranciera of Villa Borghese, visit the exhibition Manuel Felisi 1:1 which will lead visitors to discover the works of the artist: a contemporary "bestiary" with animals reproduced in natural size (with accompaniment in Italian sign language). Also at 10.30 at the Capitoline Museums - Villa Caffarelli will be held in Fidia, all the colors of perfection, guided tour of the exhibition in progress with deepening on the theme of polychromy on ancient works. To follow an activity in which visitors can try using color. In Casina del Cardinal Bessarione the children's workshop is planned Discovering a Casina to rediscover the history of this place through the five senses. At 11 p.m. at the Museo dell'Ara Pacis children will be able to participate in the workshop 21 April, a special birthday! To have fun in the name of history and creativity between images, characters and stories, to realize their own crown and become emperors and imperators for a day.
&nbsp;
On Sunday 21 at 15:00 at the Galleria d'Arte Moderna in via Crispi, the Group 70 tour will take place: artists, themes, techniques, to discover the protagonists and themes that have characterized the experimentation of this artistic sodalicy (with accompaniment in Italian Sign Language). At 15.15 and at 16.15 in Piazza Vittorio, free visit "La Porta Magica" and Mario's Trofei, to discover the monument characterized by enigmatic motions and hermetic signs. At 17 am at the Museum of Rome in Palazzo Braschi will be conducting the visit From the road to the Museum: the monochromes of the Casino del Bufalo to present the myth of Andromeda and Perseo in the five hundredth century monochromes of the facade of the Casino del Bufalo realized by Polidoro da Caravaggio and Maturino from Florence (with accompaniment in Italian sign language). Finally, at the same time at the Zoology Museum there is a visit to the exhibition on the eclectic Renaissance scientist Ulisse Aldrovandi.&nbsp; The festival continues until 22 April. In the morning, at 10 o'clock, who wants to discover the works of Street Art that characterize the neighborhood Square with Urban Routes. A traveling route in the historic district with an anti-fascist vocation, marked by the slowing of April 17, 1944, which is the main theme of inspiration for the works of Street art of the M.U.Ro project (with accompaniment in Italian Sign Language). At 11 am at the Mercati di Traiano - Museo dei Fori Imperiali, begins the visit "Augusto, the new founder of Rome" which tells the figure of Emperor Augustus and his attempt to appear as the new founder of the city (with accompaniment in the Italian Sign Language). The municipality remembers that for visits and meetings the reservation is mandatory at 060608 (active every day 9-19). In the Museums in the City, you can visit, in addition to the permanent collections, also the numerous temporary exhibitions currently underway, accessible by ordinary but free tariff for the owners of the MIC Card. At the Capitoline Museums (Piazza del Campidoglio 1), in the Sala degli Arazzi of the Palazzo dei Conservatori, you can admire the VRBS Roma, the golden glass depicting the goddess Rome. In Palazzo Clementino, I Colori dell'Antico is hosted. Santarelli marbles at the Capitoline Museums, a wide overview of the use of coloured marbles, from the beginning to the twentieth century. In Villa Caffarelli, the imposing reconstruction in real dimensions of the Colossus of Constantine is exposed. At the Montemartini Central (via Ostiense 106) you can visit the exhibition Uninhabitable architectures. To the Mercati di Traiano - Museo dei Fori Imperiali (via IV Novembre 94), the exhibition Imago Augusti. At the Museum of Rome in Trastevere (piazza S. Egidio, 1/b) three exhibitions to visit: Rino Gaetano, dedicated to the great songwriter who marked an era in Italian music, Hilde In Italy Art and life in the photographs of Hilde Lotz-Bauer", with 100 images created by the German photographer, pioneer of street photography, and Una movida Ba'rbara. In the rooms of the Gallery of Modern Art (via Francesco Crispi 24), the exhibition Reality Optional. Miaz Brothers with the masters of the 20th century, with works painted by the artistic duo Miaz Brothers in dialogue with a selection of masterpieces from the permanent collection.
&nbsp;
At the Napoleonic Museum (Piazza di Ponte Umberto I, 1) you can admire Giuseppe Primoli and the charm of the East. At the Carlo Bilotti Museum, Aranciera di Villa Borghese (via Fiorello La Guardia 6 - avenue dell'Aranciera 4) the exhibition Manuel Felisi 1:1. Duplice offer for the Museums of Villa Torlonia: at the Casino dei Principi the anthological exhibition Giancarla Frare - Living the distance; in Casina delle Civette the exhibition "In the sign of Cambellotti". There are also initiatives: Fidia, housed in the rooms of Villa Caffarelli; Ukiyoe. The Fluctuating World. Visions from Japan, to the Museum of Rome at Palazzo Braschi; "Giacomo Matteotti. Life and death of a father of Democracy", at the Museum of Rome at Palazzo Braschi; "Beyond space, beyond time." The dream of Ulisse Aldrovandi, at the Civic Museum of Zoology. Immancabile, especially for tourists the "Circo Maximo Experience", immersive visit of the Circus Maximus in reality, increased and virtual. But Rome, as we know, is not just culture and art. It's music, sport, football with the tifo at the same time power for two teams engaged in an eternal derby playing tricks: Roma and Lazio. The first, yellow and red as the colors of Rome, the second in white and blue, which claims to be born before. Rome is traffic, ztl, metro and yards that the Romans have "adopted" with patience and irony, aware of being in a Capital that wants to renew itself. It is the "Cupolone" that at sunset colored orange, is the coming Jubilee, the Colosseum that looks all from the top of its majesticity. Rome is also food, sweetness and golosity by bars and restaurants. It's tradition of carbonara, cacio and pepper, artichoke to the giudia, fillets of baccala' and suppli', pine, tortino alici and indivia, ice creams, tart visciole and ricotta, donambelline to the wine of the Castles, husband with cream... Wonderful wishes of eternal city.&nbsp;

