AGI -&nbsp; "The bloodline of the defendant on the broken glass is the signature of the murder." Thus the Father Alberto Sgambati in the requisite asked and obtained from the court of appeal of the Eagle (presied by Armanda Servino), the sentence to the life of the thirty-year-old Alessandro Chiarelli, accused of having killed on November 25, 2021 in Popoli, (Pescara) with 17 knives, Fulvio Declerch, 54 years old. The second-degree college confirmed the first sentence, absolving the defendant from the aggravating premeditation and robbing the crime of destruction of corpse in occultation. The victim's body was thrown into the river. You will have to wait for the month of July to know the reasons, but in fact the court confirmed in full the remaining three aggravating (crudelity, futile motives and handicapped defense of the offended part) evidenced first and reiterated yesterday by the representative of the public accusation who spoke of a "delitto in which the brain was used", to underline "the cold determination of the accused", after a quarrel of wine in a same drink The killer, according to what emerged from the trial, after climbing on the balcony and breaking through the window of Declerch's apartment (procuring a wound to the right hand), had clinged on him 17 times with a knife 34 cm long: on neck and chest the first 6 shots, on the face the others, "when by now the victim was on the ground and agonized", recalled in the classroom the Pg. Colpi who had led to the cut of part of an ear found on the ground by the pollutants. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
To direct the investigations on Chiarelli, not only his own burrascous past, but also the testimony of two other friends of the victim who in the evening of the murder were present at the skewer and tension between victim and defendant. Chiarelli had already presented himself with a knife, except to be brought back to reason and accompanied outside the door. He would have waited for the other two friends to leave to execute the murder. From some images a carabinieri marshal had recognized Chiarelli as the person who with a wheelbarrow had brought the body in a stretch of the Pescara river, where Declerch's body was found by a passer, and then went back, without a wheelbarrow. When investigators entered the premises of the defendant, they found shoes and clothes washed in a washing machine ( shoes of the same model of the traces found by the Carabinieri of the Ris of Rome in the apartment of the victim) and the vest (the one worn by the defendant in the evening of the murder) thrown into the trash. Both Pg and defenders (Gianluigi Tucci and Fabrizio Castellano) announced the appeal for Cassation. &nbsp;

